Melrose Walk is a residential development featuring 6 modern ultra-luxury duplex villas with open plan kitchens (fitted with integrated Smeg appliances) and generously sunlit living and dining areas with high ceilings. The bedrooms are spacious, furnished with bespoke joinery, and they come complete with en-suite bathrooms finished with high-quality material accents, from warm Oggie hardwood flooring to Eezi Quartz “Magnolia” countertops, and walk-in showers with large noir marble tiling.  The villas also have signature lighting by the renowned Stephen Pickus, and Jetmaster Amnesti Rondo fireplaces, as well as private gardens that are lushly planted with a variety of indigenous flora. According to the developer, many established trees were retained during construction, providing privacy and canopies of cool shade for inhabitants, and are home to various bird species native to the area. Also Read: Paarl Rock- Conradie Park development in Cape Town, South Africa Extra-large double garages ensure plenty of parking for residents with visitors comfortably accommodated with designated parking bays.  Melrose Walk Villas also include Biometric access, storage rooms, a centralized temperature control system, Fibre & Dstv connection, along with an array of eco-conscious systems such as warm LED lighting, eco-roof insulation, and Photovoltaic paneling for water heating, and solar-assisted electricity. Developed by Legaro Properties, an international award-winning developer of upmarket residential and commercial properties in Johannesburg, Melrose Walk development is aiming to achieve an EDGE rating from the Green Building Council of South Africa.